Date: 22 July 1812 - Size: Small - Location: Salamanca, Western
Spain\\Scenario Briefing: The Battle of Salamanca: Securing the
Arapiles - Having only surveyed the position during dusk, Wellington
failed to include the Greater Arapile inside his lines. The following
morning, however, Marmont sent Bonnet's entire division to secure
it and Wellington, judging it to close to his right flank, ordered
the 7th Cacadores to race to the hill and try to secure it before
the French reached it.\\Recommended Rules: Default - with the
following alterations - Movement Threat Disorder and Line Movement
